  <dsc><c01 id="aspace_63d4b1fd69a55f3aa430c76ac8df8e25" level="series"><did><unittitle>Account books</unittitle></did><scopecontent id="aspace_60f8346feecec3b527ffe23712edb7bd"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>NOTE: Most of the account books contain two types of entries: expenditures for groceries, household goods and supplies, clothing, drygoods, etc., in front of books; receipts mainly for glass blowing in back of books.</p></scopecontent><c02 id="aspace_114b8770e9da77150514d57455341e4b" level="item"><did><unittitle>Glass blowing receipts; firm not named. No expenditures for household, etc. Birth dates of three children noted down; year of daughter's birth not same as on loose item in folder (1860?, 1861?).</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1859-08/1861-05" type="inclusive">Aug. 1859-May 1861</unitdate><container id="aspace_1301aae52f5ffb8d3924f74b43e1eae3" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235834]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_2d28ff48d49ada96bdd3a7671e3bd913" parent="aspace_1301aae52f5ffb8d3924f74b43e1eae3" type="volume">1</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_18d95283900e26f64435df39742bb852" level="item"><did><unittitle>John M. Moore &amp; Company.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1862-10/1865-04" type="inclusive">Oct. 1862-Apr. 1865</unitdate><container id="aspace_85ba9ba58175979c62deecd6f07c2161" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235834]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_c86815b5cd7d8c22759c1d1a1bcba918" parent="aspace_85ba9ba58175979c62deecd6f07c2161" type="volume">2</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_09d7e5e71b21465a5495b8720be3c131" level="item"><did><unittitle>Moore Brothers. Dealers in Dry Goods, Groceries, Queensware, Boots &amp; Shoes, Provisions, etc., Fislerville [later Clayton], N.J.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1865-04/1867-08" type="inclusive">Apr. 1865-Aug. 1867</unitdate><container id="aspace_f2e11d95ba1af486f2467aa2a0699cc8" label=